      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to extend my sincerest gratitude for your interest in the Senior Developer role at our Austin office and for the effort you put into your application. We were truly impressed by your skills in system design and your positive cultural fit with our team. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has more experience with our specific cloud stack.\n\nWe understand that this decision may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that it was not an easy one. We were very impressed with your abilities and are confident that you will find success in your future endeavors. We will keep your resume on file for future opportunities that may align with your expertise.\n\nThank you again for your interest in joining our team. We wish you all the best in your career and hope that you continue to pursue your passion for technology.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
