      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to reach out personally to thank you for your interest in the Senior Developer role at our Austin office and for the effort you put into your application. We were truly impressed by your skills in system design and your positive cultural fit with our team. It was a pleasure getting to know you and seeing your passion for technology.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has more experience with our specific cloud stack. We understand that this decision may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that it was not an easy one. We were very impressed with your abilities and are confident that you will find success in your future endeavors. We will keep your resume on file for future opportunities that may align with your expertise.\n\nWe appreciate the time and effort you invested in the application process, and we hope that you continue to pursue your passion for technology. We wish you all the best in your career and hope that we have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
